==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Paraph
<hw>Par"aph</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F.
<ets>paraphe</ets>, <ets>parafe</ets>, contr. fr.
<ets>paragraphe</ets>.]</ety> <def>A flourish made with the pen at the
end of a signature. In the Middle Ages, this formed a sort of rude
safeguard against forgery.</def> <rj><au>Brande & C.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Paraph</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Paraph
<hw>Par"aph</hw>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p. p.</pos>
<conjf>Paraphed</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb. n.</pos>
<conjf>Paraphing</conjf>.]</vmorph> <ety>[Cf. F. <ets>parapher</ets>,
<ets>parafer</ets>.]</ety> <def>To add a paraph to; to sign, esp. with
the initials.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Parapherna</ent>⟦br⟧
